  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Bring</strong> a large pot of water to the boil for step 3</p>\r\n<p><strong>Separate</strong> the leaves of the cavolo nero and discard the stalks</p>\r\n<p><strong>Chop</strong> any large leaves into bite-size pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Remove</strong> the anchovies from the tin and chop finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> the onion<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> and slice into 1/2cm half-moons</p>\r\n<p><strong>Crush</strong> the garlic with the side of a knife, peel and chop finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Strip</strong> the thyme leaves and discard the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the cavolo nero to the pot for 2-3 min, until tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Tip: The cavolo nero will be further cooked in step 7, so aim for al-dente at this point</p>\r\n<p><strong>Remove</strong> from the pot (keeping the water boiling for step 5) with a slotted spoon and into a strainer</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Rinse</strong> the cavolo nero under cold running water until cold to the touch</p>\r\n<p><strong>Gently</strong> squeeze out the excess water and set aside in a bowl until step 7</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reserve</strong> the strainer for step 5</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the pasta to the pot of boiling water from step 3 with a pinch of salt (optional)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cook</strong> the pasta for 8-10 min or until cooked to your taste, stirring occasionally, then drain and retain a cup of pasta water</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, add 1-2 tbsp of olive oil to a non-stick pan on a medium heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the anchovies and cook for 30 sec, or until fragrant and browned, stirring constantly</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the onion and cook for 5-7 min, or until carmelized, stirring constantly</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the garlic and cook for 1 min, or until fragrant and browned slightly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the thyme and reduce the heat to low</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the drained cavolo nero and cook for 2-3 min, seperating it as you go</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> 3/4 of the double cream, stir well, and cook for 1-2 min, or until warm</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the pasta, gently fold through, and turn off the heat</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/319.-step7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the remaining cream and stir through</p>\r\n<p><strong>Gradually</strong> add a little of the reserved pasta water if a little dry</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> to your taste with salt and plenty of pepper&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
